  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  any neonate of gestational age less than 33 weeks of amenorrhea still on conventional
             assisted ventilation or HFOV (High Frequency Oscillatory Ventilation), after 14 Â± 2
             days of life

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  active infection (CRP &gt; 30 mg/L) not controlled by appropriate antibiotic treatment

          -  use of corticosteroids in the postnatal period

          -  significant neurological or malformative disease

          -  surgical intervention &lt; 72 hours

          -  refusal of parental approval
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
